.SH NAME
CSSLayerStatementRule \- CSSLayerStatementRule
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]CSSLayerStatementRule\f[B]\f[R] represents a
\f[CR]\(atlayer\f[R] statement rule.
Unlike \f[CR]CSSLayerBlockRule\f[R], it doesn\(cqt contain other rules
and merely defines one or several layers by providing their names.
.PP
This rule allows to explicitly declare the ordering layer that is in an
apparent way at the beginning of a CSS file: the layer order is defined
by the order of first occurrence of each layer name.
Declaring them with a statement allows the reader to understand the
layer order.
It also allows inline and imported layers to be interleaved, which is
not possible when using the \f[CR]CSSLayerBlockRule\f[R] syntax.
